The paper focuses on developing a taxonomy for whole-body robot configurations that use the environment to enhance stability during locomotion and manipulation tasks. This falls under the field of robotics, specifically in the area of humanoid robots. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a set of rules to store and generate new motions, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of motion capture data and segmentation techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for autonomous control of humanoid robots, which falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY).
